OL,3,CMeet Luke Akehurst: One of the North
OL,4,CEast's most controversial MPs
OL,6,FIn 2009, he developed a neurological
OL,7,Fdisorder called POEMS syndrome, and
OL,8,Fspent five months in hospital. After a
OL,9,Ffurther nine months in a wheelchair,
OL,10,Fhe now uses a walking stick.
OL,12,F"I was in hospital for five months,
OL,13,Ftreated with radiotherapy, came home
OL,14,Funable to walk, was in a wheelchair
OL,15,Ffor a year, and then the NHS taught me
OL,16,Fto walk again," he said.
OL,18,F"So if you can overcome that kind of
OL,19,Fillness, some of the political battles
OL,20,Fthat I've bought seem comparatively
OL,21,Feasy."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/8
